-----------------------------SETUP your repository on your server ----------------------------------- 
yum install git -y

------------ check git version
             git --version

----------------- set up your local repository 

- set a name that is identifiable for credit when review version history
     eg. git config --global user.name "Michael Zock"

- set an email address that will be associated with each history marker
    eg. git config --global user.email "linuxclass102022@gmail.com"

- set automatic command line coloring for Git for easy reviewing
git config --global color.ui auto
set automatic command line coloring for Git for easy reviewing

----------------------COMMAND to set-up ---------------------------------------------------
git add name
git commit -a -m "message you want"
git push origin main or branch name
git branch ster (it's to create a branch)
git branch checkout name (it's to switch branch)
git pull then name (it's to update your file before starting working)

--------------------COMMAND for your own set up-------------
ls -al ~/.ssh/
  cat ~/.ssh/
  cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
  ssh -T git@github.com
  git clone git@github.com:djangaolivier/Devops.git
  cd Devops/
  git pull origin master

